# UI styling and components

## Tailwind (NativeWind)

- **Always** style UI with **Tailwind via NativeWind** (`className`, `cn()` from `@/lib/utils`, `cva` where variants help). Do not introduce `StyleSheet.create` or ad-hoc inline `style={{}}` for layout, spacing, colors, or typography unless a platform or library API requires it (then keep it minimal and document why).
- Use **`tailwind-merge`** patterns already in the repo so classes compose safely.

## Design system (`global.css`)

- Treat [`global.css`](global.css) as the source of truth for **semantic tokens**: light/dark `:root` variables (`--background`, `--foreground`, `--primary`, `--card`, `--muted`, `--destructive`, `--border`, `--radius`, chart colors, etc.) and **JetBrains Mono** for `--font-sans` / `--font-mono`.
- In components, prefer **semantic Tailwind classes** wired in [`tailwind.config.js`](tailwind.config.js) (e.g. `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `bg-primary`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border-border`, `rounded-lg` with `radius` tokens)—not one-off hex colors—unless adding a token to the design system is explicitly part of the task.

## Naming

- **File names** for components use **kebab-case** (e.g. `race-summary-card.tsx`, `driver-row.tsx`). **Exported React components** use **PascalCase** (`RaceSummaryCard`, `DriverRow`) per React conventions.

## Reusable UI

- When building patterns that appear more than once, **extract** them into **small, meaningful** components under `components/` (and `components/ui/` for primitives), with clear names and props.
- Prefer patterns and primitives aligned with **[React Native Reusables](https://reactnativereusables.com/)** for new UI—match existing pieces in `components/ui/` first, then add or adapt following that system so behavior and styling stay consistent.

## Examples

```tsx
// Prefer
<View className="rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-4">
  <Text className="text-card-foreground">...</Text>
</View>

// Avoid for ordinary layout/visual styling
<View style={{ padding: 16, borderRadius: 8, backgroundColor: '#fff' }}>
```
